CREATE TABLE players (player_id INT PRIMARY KEY, player_name VARCHAR(50), team_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (team_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id));

CREATE TABLE matches (match_id INT PRIMARY KEY, match_date DATE, team1_id INT, team2_id INT, winner_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (team1_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id), FOREIGN KEY (team2_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id), FOREIGN KEY (winner_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id));</t><s>SELECT * FROM teams;</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE teams (team_id INT PRIMARY KEY, team_name VARCHAR(50));

CREATE TABLE players (player_id INT PRIMARY KEY, player_name VARCHAR(50), team_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (team_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id));

CREATE TABLE matches (match_id INT PRIMARY KEY, match_date DATE, team1_id INT, team2_id INT, winner_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (team1_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id), FOREIGN KEY (team2_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id), FOREIGN KEY (winner_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id));</t><s>select * from teams;</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE teams (team_id INT PRIMARY KEY, team_name VARCHAR(50));

CREATE TABLE matches (match_id INT PRIMARY KEY, match_date DATE, team1_id INT, team2_id INT, winner_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (team1_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id), FOREIGN KEY (team2_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id), FOREIGN KEY (winner_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id));

CREATE TABLE teams (team_id INT PRIMARY KEY, team_name VARCHAR(50));

CREATE TABLE matches (match_id INT PRIMARY KEY, match_date DATE, team1_id INT, team2_id INT, winner_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (team1_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id), FOREIGN KEY (team2_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id), FOREIGN KEY (winner_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id));</t><s>SELECT t1.team_name AS team1_name, t2.team_name AS team2_name FROM matches m JOIN teams t1 ON m.team1_id = t1.team_id JOIN teams t2 ON m.team2_id = t2.team_id;</s>

CREATE TABLE tournament (tournament_id INT PRIMARY KEY, tournament_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, sport VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL)

CREATE TABLE player (player_id INT PRIMARY KEY, player_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, team_id INT NOT NULL, age INT) REFERENCES team(team_id)

CREATE TABLE match (match_id INT PRIMARY KEY, match_date DATE NOT NULL, team1_id INT NOT NULL, team2_id INT NOT NULL) REFERENCES team(team_id)</t><s>select match_date, team1_id, team2_id from match</s>

CREATE TABLE player (player_id INT PRIMARY KEY, player_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, team_id INT NOT NULL, age INT) REFERENCES team(team_id)

CREATE TABLE tournament (tournament_id INT PRIMARY KEY, tournament_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, sport VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL)

CREATE TABLE match (match_id INT PRIMARY KEY, match_date DATE NOT NULL, team1_id INT NOT NULL, team2_id INT NOT NULL) REFERENCES team(team_id)</t><s>SELECT match_date, team1_id, team2_id FROM match</s>

CREATE TABLE match (match_id INT PRIMARY KEY, match_date DATE NOT NULL, team1_id INT NOT NULL, team2_id INT NOT NULL) REFERENCES team(team_id)

CREATE TABLE stadium (stadium_id INT PRIMARY KEY, stadium_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, city VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL)</t><s>select team_name, player_name from team inner join player on team.team_id = player.team_id</s>

CREATE TABLE match (match_id INT PRIMARY KEY, match_date DATE NOT NULL, team1_id INT NOT NULL, team2_id INT NOT NULL) REFERENCES team(team_id)

CREATE TABLE player (player_id INT PRIMARY KEY, player_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, team_id INT NOT NULL, age INT) REFERENCES team(team_id)

CREATE TABLE tournament (tournament_id INT PRIMARY KEY, tournament_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, sport VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL)</t><s>select team_name, player_name from team inner join player on team.team_id = player.team_id</s>

CREATE TABLE team (team_id INT PRIMARY KEY, team_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, sport VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL)

CREATE TABLE tournament (tournament_id INT PRIMARY KEY, tournament_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, sport VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL)</t><s>SELECT team_name, match_date FROM team INNER JOIN match ON team.team_id = match.team1_id</s>

CREATE TABLE match (match_id INT PRIMARY KEY, match_date DATE NOT NULL, team1_id INT NOT NULL, team2_id INT NOT NULL) REFERENCES team(team_id)

CREATE TABLE player (player_id INT PRIMARY KEY, player_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, team_id INT NOT NULL, age INT) REFERENCES team(team_id)

CREATE TABLE stadium (stadium_id INT PRIMARY KEY, stadium_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, city VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL)</t><s>SELECT team_name, match_date FROM team INNER JOIN match ON team.team_id = match.team1_id</s>

CREATE TABLE tournament (tournament_id INT PRIMARY KEY, tournament_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, sport VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL)

CREATE TABLE stadium (stadium_id INT PRIMARY KEY, stadium_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, city VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL)

CREATE TABLE team (team_id INT PRIMARY KEY, team_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, sport VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL)

CREATE TABLE player (player_id INT PRIMARY KEY, player_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, team_id INT NOT NULL, age INT) REFERENCES team(team_id)

CREATE TABLE match (match_id INT PRIMARY KEY, match_date DATE NOT NULL, team1_id INT NOT NULL, team2_id INT NOT NULL) REFERENCES team(team_id)</t><s>select count(*) from match</s>
